The paper discusses cognitive architectures, which are models of human cognition, and their practical applications. This falls under the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE), as cognitive architectures often use neural networks to model cognitive processes. The paper also discusses attention mechanisms and human-computer interaction, which fall under the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the interdisciplinary nature of cognitive architecture research, which could fall under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
